{"source_key":"sha256-c8597aca71664a84bdd657ea13dadbd3","record_index":1172,"record_hash":"sha256:331a2899b7ff948895830b2b53c3669324ea2eeb327506b7d6c4b46cdce0260d","timestamp":"2026-05-20T02:24:31.771Z","kind":"tool_result","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:function_call_output","role":null,"text":"{\"status\":{\"[REDACTED:entropy]\":{\"completed\":\"Verdict: the turn layer is the right shape, but v1 is still too fuzzy around atomic writes, target canonicalization, and “review sharing” privacy. Fix those before coding or this will sprawl.\\n\\n**Recommended Changes**\\n- Make every metadata write part of `apply_edits`, or admit session/source metadata is non-atomic. Current code writes session/source keys before the transcript batch at [gitmeta.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs:101), so the proposal needs to stop using `set_record`/plain `set` in the capture path unless GitMeta supports them as edits.\\n- Pin the exact `git-meta-lib` rev, not just “containing PR #83”. Current pin lacks `MetaEdit::SetValue` at [Cargo.toml](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/Cargo.toml:15). I checked [git-meta PR #83](https://github.com/git-meta/git-meta/pull/83); it merged May 20, 2026 and adds the needed API.\\n- Define key formats once. The doc mixes `sha256-...`, `sha256:...`, and “32 lowercase hex chars”. Pick `sha256-<trunc128hex>` for session/source/turn keys and `sha256:<fullhex>` or similar for record hashes.\\n- Hash/escape change keys too. `ChangeId` can be arbitrary bytes, not guaranteed compact/safe text ([change_id.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-core/src/change_id.rs:17)). Treat branch/review/change index keys the same: hash key material, keep readable value in `observed_targets`.\\n- Do not assume PR review keys can be canonicalized as `github-pr:owner/repo#n` from workspace state. GitButler currently exposes `pr_number` / `review_id`, but owner/repo/provider may not be present in the snapshot path. Add explicit fallback keys like `pull-request:<remote-url-hash>#<n>` or `gitbutler-review:<id>`.\\n- The “shared workspace/head-info API” assumption is real risk. `but-api` prunes to entrypoint at [workspace.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-api/src/legacy/workspace.rs:30), while the proposal explicitly needs unpruned multi-stack visibility. Use `but_workspace::head_info` directly behind an agentlog snapshot adapter.\\n- Define which commits get kept under the 100-commit cap: tip-first, first-parent, per segment. Also relax exact `commit_count` / `file_count` if computing totals requires walking huge history; “at least cap+1” is enough for scoring.\\n- Add separators between every record hash in the turn-key hash input. `session + NUL + source + NUL + joined_hashes` is avoidably brittle.\\n- Treat backfill as a handoff problem. One giant backfill turn is okay for storage, bad for UI; require provider/user-message grouping in records before review sharing depends on it.\\n- Make review-sharing exposure rules a v1 decision, not a later question. Transcript text, tool input, branch names, file paths, PR IDs, and change IDs are all sensitive enough that “repo metadata boundary” is not the same as “safe web review link.”\\n\\n**Scoring / Index Notes**\\nThe branch/review/change index strategy is good for candidate discovery. No path index in v1 is the right call.\\n\\nBut be explicit that file-overlap evidence can only boost candidates found by branch/review/change indexes. If a session only matches by paths and never observed the queried target, v1 will miss it. That’s acceptable, but product should know.\\n\\nAlso keep `TurnSummary` boring. The proposed summary shape is fine; don’t add targets/files there. `TurnDetail.observed_targets` should be the verification source, and read-time scoring should phrase results as “observed around this work,” not “caused this work.”\"}},\"timed_out\":false}","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-20T0